1494:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/tasks.c ****          * been assigned a priority above the configured maximum system call
1495:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/tasks.c ****          * priority.  Only FreeRTOS functions that end in FromISR can be called
1496:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/tasks.c ****          * from interrupts  that have been assigned a priority at or (logically)
1497:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/tasks.c ****          * below the maximum system call interrupt priority.  FreeRTOS maintains a
1498:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/tasks.c ****          * separate interrupt safe API to ensure interrupt entry is as fast and as
1499:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/tasks.c ****          * simple as possible.  More information (albeit Cortex-M specific) is
